## 1. Codemod Tools

PatternFly provides **4 codemod tools** to automate migration:

| Tool | Command | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| **pf-codemods** (main) | `npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path> --v6` | Fixes React component API changes |
| **class-name-updater** | See [README](https://github.com/patternfly/pf-codemods/tree/main/packages/class-name-updater) | Renames `pf-v5` CSS classes to `pf-v6` |
| **tokens-update** | Included in pf-codemods `--v6` | Updates global CSS variables & React tokens |
| **css-vars-updater** | See [README](https://github.com/patternfly/pf-codemods/tree/main/packages/css-vars-updater) | Updates CSS variables in `.css`, `.scss`, `.md` files |

### Recommended Order:
1. Update dependencies to PF6 versions first
2. Run `npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path> --v6` (without `--fix` first to review)
3. Run again with `--fix` flag
4. Run `class-name-updater` with `--v6 --fix`
5. Run `css-vars-updater` for non-React files
6. Run `--only data-codemods-cleanup` to remove temporary `data-codemods` markers
7. Manual cleanup

