<!-- 6.3 Modal -->
<a id="det-modal"></a>
<details open>
  <summary>6.3 Modal Migration <span class="badge badge-red" style="margin-left:8px">Bug on B1</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>The old <code>Modal</code> is deprecated тЖТ moved to <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code></li>
      <li>The new composable <code>Modal</code> (from <code>/next</code>) is promoted to <code>@patternfly/react-core</code></li>
      <li>With the new Modal: the <code>title</code> prop does NOT exist тАФ title goes in <code>&lt;ModalHeader title="..." /&gt;</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Branch Comparison</h4>
    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-col loser">
        <div class="cmp-header">pf-codemods-053126-0326</div>
        <p><strong>Strategy:</strong> Moved <code>Modal</code> + <code>ModalVariant</code> imports to <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code> in 5 files.</p>
        <p style="color:var(--red)"><strong>Bug in SilencesUtils.tsx:</strong></p>
        <pre><code>&lt;Modal isOpen={isOpen} position="top"
  title={t('Expire silence')}          тЖР OLD deprecated prop
  variant={ModalVariant.small}&gt;
  &lt;ModalHeader title={t('Expire Silence')} /&gt;  тЖР NEW prop
  &lt;ModalBody&gt;...</code></pre>
        <p>The <code>title</code> prop on <code>&lt;Modal&gt;</code> is <strong>duplicated</strong> with the <code>&lt;ModalHeader&gt;</code>. Using the deprecated import means the old <code>title</code> prop is active, so the title will render twice тАФ once from Modal's old rendering and once from ModalHeader.</p>
        <p><strong>Also a strategic concern:</strong> Using <code>/deprecated</code> imports is a backward step. These Modals already used the new composable API (<code>ModalHeader</code>/<code>ModalBody</code>/<code>ModalFooter</code>), so moving them to deprecated is wrong тАФ they should stay on the promoted API.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-col winner">
        <div class="cmp-header">semver/goose/053126-0254</div>
        <p><strong>Strategy:</strong> Kept Modals on the promoted <code>@patternfly/react-core</code> import (correct тАФ they already use the composable pattern). Removed the stale <code>title</code> prop from <code>&lt;Modal&gt;</code> in <code>SilencesUtils.tsx</code> and <code>custom-time-range-modal.tsx</code>.</p>
        <pre><code>// SilencesUtils.tsx тАФ correct
&lt;Modal isOpen={isOpen} position="top"
  variant={ModalVariant.small}&gt;
  &lt;ModalHeader title={t('Expire Silence')} /&gt;
  &lt;ModalBody&gt;...</code></pre>
        <p><strong>Also restructured form-in-modal pattern</strong> in <code>dashboard-action-modals.tsx</code>: moved <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> inside <code>&lt;ModalBody&gt;</code> with <code>form="id"</code> attribute on submit button тАФ aligning with PF6 recommended Modal form pattern.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:12px">
      <strong>Score:</strong>
      <span class="badge badge-red">pf-codemods: 0/3</span> тАФ Wrong direction (deprecated) + introduces a rendering bug;
      <span class="badge badge-green">semver/goose: 3/3</span> тАФ Correct approach, removes stale props, restructures forms properly.
    </div>
    <div class="winner-tag b2" style="margin-top:8px">Winner: semver/goose</div>
  </div>
</details>

