  <h3 style="margin-top:20px">Remaining Work for semver/goose (before merge)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Verify StackItem <code>component</code> prop:</strong> In <code>time-dropdowns.tsx</code> and <code>dashboard-header.tsx</code>, the <code>component</code> prop receives JSX elements. PF6 <code>component</code> typically expects a string (<code>"div"</code>, <code>"section"</code>). Test these at runtime or refactor back to children.</li>
    <li><strong>Remove duplicate Cypress selectors:</strong> In <code>utility-commands.ts</code> and <code>common.ts</code>, selectors like <code>.pf-v6-c-alert, .pf-v6-c-alert</code> list the same class twice. Harmless but untidy.</li>
    <li><strong>Consider removing <code>PF_THEME_DARK_CLASS_V5</code> constant:</strong> In <code>usePatternflyTheme.ts</code>, both V5 and V6 constants now hold <code>'pf-v6-theme-dark'</code>. Remove the V5 constant to avoid confusion.</li>
    <li><strong>Separate <code>processAlerts.spec.ts</code> change:</strong> The test timestamp change is unrelated to PF migration тАФ consider a separate commit.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 style="margin-top:20px">Why pf-codemods Falls Short</h3>
  <p>This branch appears to be raw codemod output with minimal manual follow-up. The <code>pf-codemods</code> tool correctly identified 5 Modal files for the deprecated import path, but:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>These Modals were <em>already on the new composable API</em>, making the deprecated import path wrong</li>
    <li>The codemod did not remove the stale <code>title</code> prop, creating a rendering bug</li>
    <li>The EmptyState <code>titleText</code> codemod left <code>&lt;Title&gt;</code> elements as the value тАФ the codemod may have only partially applied</li>
    <li>No CSS class migration, no icon prop migration, no Popper migration, no table structure updates</li>
    <li>The branch is a starting point at best, not a complete migration</li>
  </ul>
